'''''Star Wars Insider'' 83''' was the 83rd issue of ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'', released on [[July 20]] [[2005]].

==Contents==
===Features===
*"[[Ground Assault: The Vehicles of Episode III]]" {{C|by [[Daniel Wallace]]}}
*:<small>To win the war for galactic supremacy, it helps to have a few good men and some seriously powerful machinery on your side. Of course, fighting on the side of an omniscient [[Sith Lord/Legends|Sith Lord]] helps too.</small>
*"[[The Art of Revenge of the Sith]], Part 1" {{C|by [[Jonathan W. Rinzler]]}}
*:<small>[[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith|Episode III]] proved to be a feast for the visual senses thanks to the brilliance of director [[George Lucas]] and a few concept artists. In a bold move, ''Insider'' was able to breach [[Lucasfilm]]'s art vault to bring you these exclusive images, and we didn't even have to harm any [[Clone trooper/Legends|clone troopers]] to do it.</small>
*"[[20 Most Memorable Moments of the Expanded Universe]]" {{C|by [[Abel G. Peña|Abel Peña]] and [[Enrique Guerrero]]}}
*:<small>Now that the cinema saga is complete, fans will want to get up to speed about all the happenings in the [[Star Wars Legends|Expanded Universe]]. ''Insider'' is pleased to offer up our 20 favorite moments from the past 28 years. We can even throw in a few not-so-great moments. We must warn you that there are many spoilers contained within-enter at your own risk!</small>
*"[[Multiple Personality]]" {{C|by [[Brett Rector]]}}
*:<small>The chances of appearing in a ''[[Star Wars]]'' film were pretty slim to begin with, but to appear in all three [[Prequel trilogy|prequels]]—as up to four characters no less—is just simply unheard of. That is, unless you are [[Silas Carson]].</small>
*"[[Spray Paint and Stormtroopers: Star Wars Street Art|Spray Paint and Stormtroopers: ''Star Wars'' Street Art]]" {{C|by [[Bonnie Burton]]}}
*:<small>[[George Lucas]] started a film making revolution when he released ''[[Star Wars]]'' back in [[1977]]. Who knew that his creative fire would spark an urban revolution as well?</small>
*"[[MedStar: Intermezzo]]" {{C|by [[Michael Reaves|Michael Reeves]] and [[Steve Perry]]}}
*:<small>Battlefield surgeon [[Jos Vondar]] faces a moral dilemma when he must opperate on a [[Zabrak/Legends|Zabrak]] mercenary who killed his best friend.</small>

